DEADLINE EXTENSION
***********************************************************************
Following a number of requests, the deadline for submitting full papers=20
to IWCS-7 has been extended to October 5, 2006.
See the revised timetable below.
***********************************************************************


                    Seventh International Workshop on

                       =20
                             (IWCS-7)

             January 10-12, 2007, Tilburg, The Netherlands

                            -------------
                             Endorsed by SIGSEM,
        the ACL Special Interest Group in Computational Semantics

                            -------------


                FIRST ANNOUNCEMENT AND CALL FOR PAPERS

Tilburg University will host the Seventh International Workshop on
Computational Semantics (IWCS-7), which will take place on 10-12
January 2007. The aim of the workshop is to bring together
researchers interested in any aspects of the computation, annotation,
extraction, and representation of meaning in natural language,=20
in multimedia objects, and in multimodal messages.


                          TOPICS OF INTEREST

Areas of special interest for the workshop will be computational
aspects of semantic theories; theoretical aspects of the design of
language understanding systems and systems for multimodal
communication; and semantic annotation of natural language and
multimodal utterances. Papers are invited that are concerned with
topics in these and closely related areas, including, but not=20
limited to, the following:

  * construction of representations of meaning in natural language
  * methodologies and practices for semantic annotation
  * modelling and using context in semantic interpretation
  * machine learning of semantic structures
  * formal and computational methods in lexical semantics

  * computing meaning in multimodal interaction
  * construction and use of underspecified semantic representations=20
  * semantic concepts and ontologies
  * approaches to textual entailment
  * the semantics and pragmatics of dialogue acts

  * the semantic web and natural language processing
  * semantic aspects of language generation
  * the semantics-pragmatics interface in computational perspective
  * semantic relations in discourse and dialogue
  * shallow and deep semantic processing and reasoning



                         INVITED SPEAKERS=20

      Johan Bos (La Sapienza University, Rome)
      Paul Buitelaar (German Institute for AI, Saarbruecken)
      Makoto Kanazawa (National Institute for Informatics, Tokyo)



   ISO/SIGSEM JOINT WORKING GROUP MEETING ON SEMANTIC ANNOTATION

Immediately preceding IWCS-7, on 8-9 January 2007, a joint meeting=20
will be held of the ACL-SIGSEM Working Group on the Representation=20
of Multimodal Semantic Information and of ISO TC 37/SC 4 on the=20
Representation of Semantic Content. This meeting will be devoted to
the development of methodologies, tools, and concepts for semantic=20
annotation, focusing in particular on:=20
(1) the definition of an ISO standard for the annotation of temporal=20
information; and=20
(2) the development of an on-line registry of concepts for semantic=20
annotation for semantic roles, referential relations, dialogue acts,=20
and discourse relations.=20
This meeting will be open to (a limited number of) IWCS-7 participants.=20
For more information see http://let.uvt.nl/research/ti/iso-tdg3 and=20
http://let.uvt.nl/research/TI/sigsem/wg




                       PROGRAMME COMMITTEE

              James Allen            Alex Lascarides
              Patrick Blackburn      Kiyong Lee=20
              Johan Bos              Dan Moldovan
              Harry Bunt (chair)     Reinhard Muskens
              Nicoletta Calzolari    Martha Palmer
              Robin Cooper           Manfred Pinkal
              Kees van Deemter       Massimo Poesio
              Jan van Eijck          Steve Pulman
              Dafydd Gibbon          James Pustejovsky
              Jerry Hobbs            Alan Ramsay
              Ed Hovy                Laurent Romary
              Daniel Kayser          Patrick Saint Dizier
              Paul Mc Kevitt         Carl Vogel
              Alexander Koller       Bonnie Webber
              Emiel Krahmer         =20


                         ORGANISING COMMITTEE

              Harry Bunt             Reinhard Muskens
              Jeroen Geertzen        Amanda Schiffrin
              Simon Keizer           Elias Thijsse=20
              Lauraine Sinay (secr.) Femke Wieme (secr.)


                       SUBMISSION REQUIREMENTS

Three types of submission are solicited: full papers, short papers,
and project abstracts.

Full papers
-----------
Full papers are original papers of maximally 12 pages, that will be=20
published in the workshop proceedings and will have a full oral=20
presentation of about 30 minutes at the workshop.

Short papers
------------
Short papers are mini-papers of maximally 4 pages, that will be=20
published in the workshop proceedings and have a very brief ('flash')=20
oral presentation at the workshop. Authors of short papers are=20
invited to also put up a poster and participate in a poster session.

Project abstracts
-----------------
Project abstracts are brief descriptions of 2 pages of ongoing,
recently completed, or starting projects. They will be published in
the workshop proceedings and will be presented in a poster session.

Submission formats
------------------
Submission must be done through the online submission system at=20
www.easychair.org/IWCS7/ All submissions should be marked as being=20
a full paper, a short paper, or a project abstract, by adding to the=20
paper title the postfix (FP), (SP), or (PA) when entering the title=20
of the submission in the online submission system. See also the=20
IWCS-7 website http://let.uvt.nl/research/ti/sigsem/iwcs/iwcs7 for=20
information on submission formats.=20
The page limits presuppose standard 11 point Computer Modern font.=20
Final versions of accepted contributions will have to be submitted=20
as LaTeX source files to facilitate publication of the proceedings;=20
we also aim at publishing a selection of accepted papers in book form
after the workshop.

Online submission website: www.easychair.org/IWCS7/

Submission deadlines
--------------------
For full papers the submission deadline is 25 September 2006; for
short papers and project abstracts the deadline is 1 November.


                           IMPORTANT DATES
REVISED TIMETABLE:
  5  October    2006 Submission of full papers
  1  November   2006 Notification of acceptance
  1  November   2006 Submission of short papers and project abstracts
  22 November   2006 Camera-ready final versions of papers due
  1 December    2006 Deadline for early registration
  8-9 January   2007 Joint Meeting of ISO TC 37/SC 4 Thematic Domain=20
                     Group on Semantic Content and ACL SIGSEM Working=20
                     Group on the Representation of Multimodal=20
                     Semantic Information
  10-12 January 2007 IWCS-7 workshop


                         FURTHER INFORMATION

Secretariat: Ms Lauraine Sinay or Ms Femke Wieme
             Department of Language and Information Science
             Tilburg University
             PO Box 90153
             5000 LE Tilburg
             The Netherlands
             Fax:   +31-13 466 28 92
             Phone: +31-13 466 30 60 or ..81 18 or ..26 68
             Email: computational.semantics@uvt.nl

Conference website: http://let.uvt.nl/research/ti/sigsem/iwcs/iwcs7
Online submission website: www.easychair.org/IWCS7/

