&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
FIRST ANNOUNCEMENT AND CALL FOR PAPERS<BR><BR>Tilburg University will =
host the=20
Seventh International Workshop on<BR>Computational Semantics (IWCS-7), =
which=20
will take place on 10-12<BR>January 2007. The aim of the workshop is to =
bring=20
together<BR>researchers interested in any aspects of the computation,=20
annotation,<BR>extraction, and representation of meaning in natural =
language,=20
<BR>in multimedia objects, and in multimodal=20
messages.<BR><BR><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=
p;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
TOPICS OF INTEREST<BR><BR>Areas of special interest for the workshop =
will be=20
computational<BR>aspects of semantic theories; theoretical aspects of =
the design=20
of<BR>language understanding systems and systems for=20
multimodal<BR>communication; and semantic annotation of natural language =

and<BR>multimodal utterances. Papers are invited that are concerned=20
with<BR>topics in these and closely related areas, including, but not=20
<BR>limited to, the following:<BR><BR>&nbsp; * construction of =
representations=20
of meaning in natural language<BR>&nbsp; * methodologies and practices =
for=20
semantic annotation<BR>&nbsp; * modelling and using context in semantic=20
interpretation<BR>&nbsp; * machine learning of semantic =
structures<BR>&nbsp; *=20
formal and computational methods in lexical semantics<BR><BR>&nbsp; * =
computing=20
meaning in multimodal interaction<BR>&nbsp; * construction and use of=20
underspecified semantic representations <BR>&nbsp; * semantic concepts =
and=20
ontologies<BR>&nbsp; * approaches to textual entailment<BR>&nbsp; * the=20
semantics and pragmatics of dialogue acts<BR><BR>&nbsp; * the semantic =
web and=20
natural language processing<BR>&nbsp; * semantic aspects of language=20
generation<BR>&nbsp; * the semantics-pragmatics interface in =
computational=20
perspective<BR>&nbsp; * semantic relations in discourse and =
dialogue<BR>&nbsp; *=20
shallow and deep semantic processing and=20
reasoning<BR><BR><BR><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&=
nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
INVITED SPEAKERS <BR><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Johan Bos (La =
Sapienza=20
University, Rome)<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Paul Buitelaar =
(German=20
Institute for AI, Saarbruecken)<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Makoto =

Kanazawa (National Institute for Informatics, =
Tokyo)<BR><BR><BR><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
ISO/SIGSEM JOINT WORKING GROUP MEETING ON SEMANTIC =
ANNOTATION<BR><BR>Immediately=20
preceding IWCS-7, on 8-9 January 2007, a joint meeting <BR>will be held =
of the=20
ACL-SIGSEM Working Group on the Representation <BR>of Multimodal =
Semantic=20
Information and of ISO TC 37/SC 4 on the <BR>Representation of Semantic =
Content.=20
This meeting will be devoted to<BR>the development of methodologies, =
tools, and=20
concepts for semantic <BR>annotation, focusing in particular on: <BR>(1) =
the=20
definition of an ISO standard for the annotation of temporal =
<BR>information;=20
and <BR>(2) the development of an on-line registry of concepts for =
semantic=20
<BR>annotation for semantic roles, referential relations, dialogue acts, =
<BR>and=20
discourse relations. <BR>This meeting will be open to (a limited number =
of)=20
IWCS-7 participants. <BR>For more information see <A=20
href=3D"http://let.uvt.nl/research/ti/iso-tdg3">http://let.uvt.nl/researc=
h/ti/iso-tdg3</A>=20
and <BR><A=20
href=3D"http://let.uvt.nl/research/TI/sigsem/wg">http://let.uvt.nl/resear=
ch/TI/sigsem/wg</A><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=
p;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=
;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=20
